<DOC><DOCNO> AP880919-0118 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-19-88 1537EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p AM-BRF--OhioPoll     09-19 0130</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Ohio Poll,120</SECOND><HEAD>Dukakis Support Slides Among Ohio Voters</HEAD><DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Vice President George Bush, who once trailedMichael Dukakis by 10 percentage points in Ohio, is in a dead heatwith the Democratic nominee, according to a new poll of statevoters.   Among 667 Ohio registered voters, 43 percent support Bush, 39percent favor Dukakis and 18 percent are undecided, the Universityof Akron poll said. The 4 percentage point margin of error meansthe race is a statistical dead heat.   Since last April, Dukakis has dropped 5 points, Bush has risen 9points and the number of undecided voters declined 4 points.   The poll, commissioned by The (Akron) Beacon Journal, WKYC-TV inCleveland and WCMH-TV in Columbus, was conducted between Sept. 6-15and published Sunday.</TEXT></DOC>